Useless nonterminals

   logical_expr
   rel_expr
   bool_expr


Terminals which are not used

   TOKEN_KEYWORD
   TOKEN_ERROR
   TOKEN_EQEQ
   TOKEN_NEQ
   TOKEN_LTE
   TOKEN_GTE
   TOKEN_LT
   TOKEN_GT
   TOKEN_AND
   TOKEN_OR
   TOKEN_NOT
   TOKEN_TRUE
   TOKEN_FALSE
   TOKEN_LPAREN
   TOKEN_RPAREN


Useless rules

    9 logical_expr: logical_expr TOKEN_AND rel_expr
   10             | logical_expr TOKEN_OR rel_expr
   11             | TOKEN_NOT rel_expr
   12             | rel_expr

   13 rel_expr: expr TOKEN_LT expr
   14         | expr TOKEN_GT expr
   15         | expr TOKEN_LTE expr
   16         | expr TOKEN_GTE expr
   17         | expr TOKEN_EQEQ expr
   18         | expr TOKEN_NEQ expr
   19         | expr
   20         | bool_expr

   21 bool_expr: TOKEN_TRUE
   22          | TOKEN_FALSE


Grammar

    0 $accept: prog $end

    1 prog: expr TOKEN_SEMI

    2 expr: expr TOKEN_PLUS term
    3     | expr TOKEN_MINUS term
    4     | term

    5 term: term TOKEN_MUL factor
    6     | term TOKEN_DIV factor
    7     | factor

    8 factor: TOKEN_INT


Terminals, with rules where they appear

$end (0) 0
error (256)
TOKEN_INT (258) 8
TOKEN_PLUS (259) 2
TOKEN_MINUS (260) 3
TOKEN_MUL (261) 5
TOKEN_DIV (262) 6
TOKEN_KEYWORD (263)
TOKEN_SEMI (264) 1
TOKEN_ERROR (265)
TOKEN_EQEQ (266)
TOKEN_NEQ (267)
TOKEN_LTE (268)
TOKEN_GTE (269)
TOKEN_LT (270)
TOKEN_GT (271)
TOKEN_AND (272)
TOKEN_OR (273)
TOKEN_NOT (274)
TOKEN_TRUE (275)
TOKEN_FALSE (276)
TOKEN_LPAREN (277)
TOKEN_RPAREN (278)


Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

$accept (24)
    on left: 0
prog (25)
    on left: 1, on right: 0
expr (26)
    on left: 2 3 4, on right: 1 2 3
term (27)
    on left: 5 6 7, on right: 2 3 4 5 6
factor (28)
    on left: 8, on right: 5 6 7


state 0

    0 $accept: . prog $end

    TOKEN_INT  shift, and go to state 1

    prog    go to state 2
    expr    go to state 3
    term    go to state 4
    factor  go to state 5


state 1

    8 factor: TOKEN_INT .

    $default  reduce using rule 8 (factor)


state 2

    0 $accept: prog . $end

    $end  shift, and go to state 6


state 3

    1 prog: expr . TOKEN_SEMI
    2 expr: expr . TOKEN_PLUS term
    3     | expr . TOKEN_MINUS term

    TOKEN_PLUS   shift, and go to state 7
    TOKEN_MINUS  shift, and go to state 8
    TOKEN_SEMI   shift, and go to state 9


state 4

    4 expr: term .
    5 term: term . TOKEN_MUL factor
    6     | term . TOKEN_DIV factor

    TOKEN_MUL  shift, and go to state 10
    TOKEN_DIV  shift, and go to state 11

    $default  reduce using rule 4 (expr)


state 5

    7 term: factor .

    $default  reduce using rule 7 (term)


state 6

    0 $accept: prog $end .

    $default  accept


state 7

    2 expr: expr TOKEN_PLUS . term

    TOKEN_INT  shift, and go to state 1

    term    go to state 12
    factor  go to state 5


state 8

    3 expr: expr TOKEN_MINUS . term

    TOKEN_INT  shift, and go to state 1

    term    go to state 13
    factor  go to state 5


state 9

    1 prog: expr TOKEN_SEMI .

    $default  reduce using rule 1 (prog)


state 10

    5 term: term TOKEN_MUL . factor

    TOKEN_INT  shift, and go to state 1

    factor  go to state 14


state 11

    6 term: term TOKEN_DIV . factor

    TOKEN_INT  shift, and go to state 1

    factor  go to state 15


state 12

    2 expr: expr TOKEN_PLUS term .
    5 term: term . TOKEN_MUL factor
    6     | term . TOKEN_DIV factor

    TOKEN_MUL  shift, and go to state 10
    TOKEN_DIV  shift, and go to state 11

    $default  reduce using rule 2 (expr)


state 13

    3 expr: expr TOKEN_MINUS term .
    5 term: term . TOKEN_MUL factor
    6     | term . TOKEN_DIV factor

    TOKEN_MUL  shift, and go to state 10
    TOKEN_DIV  shift, and go to state 11

    $default  reduce using rule 3 (expr)


state 14

    5 term: term TOKEN_MUL factor .

    $default  reduce using rule 5 (term)


state 15

    6 term: term TOKEN_DIV factor .

    $default  reduce using rule 6 (term)
